library(ggrepel)

#Q1

data("mtcars")
mtcars$car <- rownames(mtcars)
ggplot(mtcars, aes(x = hp, y = mpg, color = factor(cyl), label = car)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_text_repel(size=2) +
  labs(title = "mpg vs hp", x = "hp", y = "mpg", color = "cyl") +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(size = 16, face = "bold", hjust = 0.5),
    axis.title = element_text(face = "bold"),
    panel.background = element_rect(fill = "gray90", color = NA),
    panel.grid = element_line(color = "white")
  )

#Q2

ggplot(data = diamonds, aes(x = cut, fill = color)) +
  geom_bar() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
        legend.text = element_text(size = 12),
        legend.position = "bottom")

#Q3

ggplot(data = iris, aes(x = Species, y = Sepal.Length, fill = Species)) +
  geom_boxplot(width = 0.1) +
  theme(
    panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white", color = "black", size = 1),
    axis.title.x = element_text(size = 14),
  axis.text.x = element_text(face = "italic"), 
  axis.text.y =  element_text(face = "italic")
  )

#Q4

ggplot(data = mtcars, aes(x = wt, y = mpg, color = factor(cyl))) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~cyl) +
  theme(
    strip.text = element_text(color = "darkgreen"),
    text = element_text(size = 14),
     legend.position = "bottom",
  )

#Q5

ggplot(data = mtcars, aes(x = wt, y = mpg, color = disp, size = hp)) +
  geom_point() +
  scale_color_gradient(low = "lightpink", high = "lightblue") +
  scale_size(range = c(2, 8)) +
  labs(title = "mpg vs. wt") +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom",
       plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

#Q6

ggplot(data = mtcars, aes(x = wt, y = mpg, color = factor(cyl))) +
  geom_point() +
  scale_y_log10() +
  labs(
    title = "Logarithmic Scale for MPG vs Weight",
    y = "mpg (log scale)"
  ) +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "bold")
  )

#Q7

ggplot(mtcars, aes(x = wt, y = mpg)) +
  geom_point(aes(alpha = mpg), color = "blue") +
  annotate("rect", xmin = 1, xmax = 2.2, ymin = 25, ymax = 35,
           fill = "blue", alpha = 0.1) +
  annotate("text", x = 1.6, y = 30, label = "low wt high mpg",
           size = 4, hjust = 0, fontface = "plain") +
  scale_alpha(range = c(0.1, 1)) +
  labs(title = "MPG vs Weight (Transparency by MPG)") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "bold"))

#Q8

avg_mpg <- mtcars %>%
  group_by(cyl) %>%
  summarise(mean_mpg = mean(mpg))

ggplot(avg_mpg, aes(x = factor(cyl), y = mean_mpg)) +
  geom_col(fill = "steelblue") +
  labs(title = "Average MPG by Cylinder Count",
       x = "cyl",
       y = "mean_mpg") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "bold"))

#Q9

averageprice <- diamonds %>%
  group_by(cut) %>%
  summarise(mean_price = mean(price))

ggplot(averageprice, aes(x = cut, y = mean_price, fill = cut)) +
  geom_col() +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set2") +
  labs(
    title = "Average Diamond Price by Cut Quality",
    y = "Average Price"
  ) +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "bold"))

#Q10

iris_filtered <- iris %>%
  filter(Species %in% c("setosa", "versicolor"))

ggplot(iris_filtered, aes(x = Sepal.Length, y = Petal.Length, color = Species)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE) +
  labs(
    title = "Sepal Length and Petal Length (Setosa & Versicolor)",
    x = "Sepal Length (cm)",
    y = "Petal Length (cm)"
  ) +
  theme(
    text = element_text(family = "mono"),
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "bold"),
     legend.position = "bottom")
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'
